17# include <openssl/bio.h>

19# ifdef WATT32
20/* Watt-32 uses same names */
21# undef sock_write
22# undef sock_read
23# undef sock_puts
24# define sock_write SockWrite
25# define sock_read SockRead
26# define sock_puts SockPuts
27# endif

29static int sock_write(BIO *h, const char *buf, int num);
30static int sock_read(BIO *h, char *buf, int size);
31static int sock_puts(BIO *h, const char *str);
32static long sock_ctrl(BIO *h, int cmd, long arg1, void *arg2);
33static int sock_new(BIO *h);
34static int sock_free(BIO *data);
35int BIO_sock_should_retry(int s);

37static const BIO_METHOD methods_sockp = {
38 BIO_TYPE_SOCKET,
39 "socket",
40 /* TODO: Convert to new style write function */
41 bwrite_conv,
42 sock_write,
43 /* TODO: Convert to new style read function */
44 bread_conv,
45 sock_read,
46 sock_puts,
47 NULL, /* sock_gets, */
48 sock_ctrl,
49 sock_new,
50 sock_free,
51 NULL, /* sock_callback_ctrl */
52};
53
54const BIO_METHOD *BIO_s_socket(void)
55{
56 return &methods_sockp;
57}
58
59BIO *BIO_new_socket(int fd, int close_flag)
60{
61 BIO *ret;
62
63 ret = BIO_new(BIO_s_socket());
64 if (ret == NULL)
65 return NULL;
66 BIO_set_fd(ret, fd, close_flag);
67 return ret;
68}
69
70static int sock_new(BIO *bi)
71{
72 bi->init = 0;
73 bi->num = 0;
74 bi->ptr = NULL;
75 bi->flags = 0;
76 return 1;
77}
78
79static int sock_free(BIO *a)
80{
81 if (a == NULL)
82 return 0;
83 if (a->shutdown) {
84 if (a->init) {
85 BIO_closesocket(a->num);
86 }
87 a->init = 0;
88 a->flags = 0;
89 }
90 return 1;
91}
92
93static int sock_read(BIO *b, char *out, int outl)
94{
95 int ret = 0;
96
97 if (out != NULL) {
98 clear_socket_error();
99 ret = readsocket(b->num, out, outl);
100 BIO_clear_retry_flags(b);
101 if (ret <= 0) {
102 if (BIO_sock_should_retry(ret))
103 BIO_set_retry_read(b);
104 }
105 }
106 return ret;
107}
108
109static int sock_write(BIO *b, const char *in, int inl)
110{
111 int ret;
112
113 clear_socket_error();
114 ret = writesocket(b->num, in, inl);
115 BIO_clear_retry_flags(b);
116 if (ret <= 0) {
117 if (BIO_sock_should_retry(ret))
118 BIO_set_retry_write(b);
119 }
120 return ret;
121}
122
123static long sock_ctrl(BIO *b, int cmd, long num, void *ptr)
124{
125 long ret = 1;
126 int *ip;
127
128 switch (cmd) {
129 case BIO_C_SET_FD:
130 sock_free(b);
131 b->num = *((int *)ptr);
132 b->shutdown = (int)num;
133 b->init = 1;
134 break;
135 case BIO_C_GET_FD:
136 if (b->init) {
137 ip = (int *)ptr;
138 if (ip != NULL)
139 *ip = b->num;
140 ret = b->num;
141 } else
142 ret = -1;
143 break;
144 case BIO_CTRL_GET_CLOSE:
145 ret = b->shutdown;
146 break;
147 case BIO_CTRL_SET_CLOSE:
148 b->shutdown = (int)num;
149 break;
150 case BIO_CTRL_DUP:
151 case BIO_CTRL_FLUSH:
152 ret = 1;
153 break;
154 default:
155 ret = 0;
156 break;
157 }
158 return ret;
159}
160
161static int sock_puts(BIO *bp, const char *str)
162{
163 int n, ret;
164
165 n = strlen(str);
166 ret = sock_write(bp, str, n);
167 return ret;
168}
169
170int BIO_sock_should_retry(int i)
171{
172 int err;
173
174 if ((i == 0) || (i == -1)) {
175 err = get_last_socket_error();
176
177 return BIO_sock_non_fatal_error(err);
178 }
179 return 0;
180}
181
182int BIO_sock_non_fatal_error(int err)
183{
184 switch (err) {
185# if defined(OPENSSL_SYS_WINDOWS)
186# if defined(WSAEWOULDBLOCK)
187 case WSAEWOULDBLOCK:
188# endif
189# endif
190
191# ifdef EWOULDBLOCK
192# ifdef WSAEWOULDBLOCK
193# if WSAEWOULDBLOCK != EWOULDBLOCK
194 case EWOULDBLOCK:
195# endif
196# else
197 case EWOULDBLOCK:
198# endif
199# endif
200
201# if defined(ENOTCONN)
202 case ENOTCONN:
203# endif
204
205# ifdef EINTR
206 case EINTR:
207# endif
208
209# ifdef EAGAIN
210# if EWOULDBLOCK != EAGAIN
211 case EAGAIN:
212# endif
213# endif
214
215# ifdef EPROTO
216 case EPROTO:
217# endif
218
219# ifdef EINPROGRESS
220 case EINPROGRESS:
221# endif
222
223# ifdef EALREADY
224 case EALREADY:
225# endif
226 return 1;
227 default:
228 break;
229 }
230 return 0;
231}
